It&#8217;s understood the woman had promised to give baby clothes to needy mothers as a gift for Christmas in Johannesburg's CBD. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police are investigating a case of kidnapping after a woman posing as a South African Social Security Agency (Sassa) official abducted a four-month-old baby from his mother. It s understood the woman had promised to give baby clothes to needy mothers as a gift for Christmas at the Carlton Centre in Johannesburg's CBD.She then disappeared with the infant.The police s Xoli Mbele says officers are now searching for the kidnapper. We are appealing to the public that if they saw a female that was never pregnant but is now carrying a child, they must inform their nearest police station. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)